name: Enlabs
overview:
EnLabs has been operational since December 1 in Rome. It ‘s the first incubator open to all technology start-ups and not, like those existing in Silicon Valley. The initiative starts from a business man, Luigi Capello, formerly Business Angel who began a career in investing between Italy and the United States, particularly in the Silicon Valley and was able to appreciate the validity and operation of these structures.

The incubator is located in Via Montebello 8 close to Termini train station, in an area of 400 square meters . We want to collect all the ideas / startups and help them in the process of growth and international expansion. The space has also over 40 desks 24 / 7 for cowork hosting open to everyone.
